Evaporation from saline water bodies depends on meteorological variables, but also on the salinity and the ionic composition. As the salinity increases, the free energy of the water molecules is reduced, resulting in a decrease in the saturation vapor pressure above the water surface and thus a decrease in evaporation42,43. Here, the relationship of actual salt water evaporation (Esal) to freshwater evaporation (Efresh) can be represented by the salinity dependent empirical ratio α42,43, Eq. (2).2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
